<subSubSection pageId="375" pageNumber="376" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="375" pageNumber="376">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="375" pageNumber="376">
About 15 species in the Nearctic (one northwestern species), Oriental (one species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1921" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="375" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitalisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="375" pageNumber="376">Bembidion vitalisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Andrewes from Laos), and Palaearctic (14 species) Regions. Some of the species included by Lorenz (2005: 229) in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Ocydromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="375" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="375" pageNumber="376">Ocydromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to this subgenus according to Toledano (2000: 66).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
